title: The Ron-Ron The Producer & JoogSzn Interview: Losing Drakeo, Shoreline Mafia & More
description:
Ron-Ron and Joog talk about their come-up, working with Drakeo, Shoreline, Remble, never choosing sides, building relationships in the industry, knowing the business, and more! https://www.instagram.com/ronronthepr... https://www.instagram.com/joogszn/ ----- 00:00 Intro 0:33 - Last interview with RonRon was in 2017. Being one of the main producers of the new LA sound 5:37 - First connecting with Shoreline Mafia and AceGotBands 6:40 - Explaining the difference between a producer and a beatmaker. Producing for 03Greedo and Shoreline Mafia for free 7:48 - Joog won’t reveal his “backend hustle” that sent him to jail 8:28 - Joog explains how he first connected with Drakeo the Ruler. Met before he got locked up. Recorded Drakeo’s jail tape over the phone while he was locked up 11:02 - Joog won’t reveal how he made Drakeo’s jail verses sound so good. Had a dream about how to mix the album 16:10 - Crazy 13-hour process of recording Drakeo’s jail phone verses 5 minutes at a time 16:45 - Importance of working for free as a producer to build your name up. Taking a piece of the backend instead of asking for an advance 21:10 - Working with wack rappers. Dealing with gang politics as a producer in LA 23:11 - RonRon never fell out with Shoreline Mafia. They fell out with each other but RonRon is still cool with everybody 23:42 - RonRon explains the misunderstanding that led to him calling out OhGeesy on Twitter, taking the high road to mending their relationship 44:19 - Difficulty of working with LA artists like AzChike and Rucci while also working with Drakeo. Still having a good relationship with people from all sides 47:15 - Not allowing artists to press them over politics. Not banging but being very familiar with how gangs work from growing up in LA. Both RonRon's parents gangbang 53:15 - Adam refuses to rap. Adam: “When I start rapping the m*rder rate goes up” ----- Shout to our Partners at Gamer Supps!
